time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut @potato{2} into wedges.

Place on lined #oven tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%drizzle}, sprinkle with @crispy seasoning{1%sachet} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and toss to coat.

Bake until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

When wedges have ~{10%minutes} remaining, set your #air fryer{} to 200°C.

Place @bean, lentil and zucchini patties{2} in #air fryer basket{} and cook until browned and heated through, ~{10-12%minutes} (Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

> TIP: No air fryer? Place bean, lentil & zucchini patties on a lined oven tray. Cook patties for 10-15 minutes until cooked through. (Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

While patties are cooking, halve @bake-at-home burger buns{2} and bake directly on a #wire oven rack{} until heated through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Thinly slice @tomato{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds.

Slice @lemon{1} into wedges.

Spread bun bases with @hummus{1%packet} then top with patties, tomato and @rocket{1%packet}.

Crumble @fetta cubes{1%packet} and squeeze over some lemon juice over the rocket.

Serve with crispy wedges and any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!